CSS animations can be created using two main approaches: **Transitions** and **Keyframe Animations**. Here's how to use both:

## 1. CSS Transitions
Transitions animate changes between two states when triggered by events like hover, focus, or class changes.

### Basic Syntax:
```css
.element {
  transition: property duration timing-function delay;
}
```

### Example:
```css
.button {
  background-color: blue;
  transition: background-color 0.3s ease;
}

.button:hover {
  background-color: red;
}
```

### Multiple Properties:
```css
.box {
  width: 100px;
  height: 100px;
  background-color: blue;
  transition: all 0.5s ease-in-out;
}

.box:hover {
  width: 200px;
  height: 200px;
  background-color: red;
  transform: rotate(45deg);
}
```

## 2. CSS Keyframe Animations
Keyframes allow you to create more complex animations with multiple steps.

### Basic Syntax:
```css
@keyframes animationName {
  0% { /* starting styles */ }
  50% { /* middle styles */ }
  100% { /* ending styles */ }
}

.element {
  animation: animationName duration timing-function delay iteration-count direction;
}
```

### Example:
```css
@keyframes slideIn {
  0% {
    transform: translateX(-100px);
    opacity: 0;
  }
  100% {
    transform: translateX(0);
    opacity: 1;
  }
}

.animated-element {
  animation: slideIn 1s ease-out;
}
```

## Common Animation Properties

### Timing Functions:
- `ease` - slow start, fast middle, slow end
- `ease-in` - slow start
- `ease-out` - slow end
- `ease-in-out` - slow start and end
- `linear` - constant speed
- `cubic-bezier(x1, y1, x2, y2)` - custom curve

### Animation Properties:
```css
.element {
  animation-name: myAnimation;
  animation-duration: 2s;
  animation-timing-function: ease-in-out;
  animation-delay: 0.5s;
  animation-iteration-count: infinite; /* or a number */
  animation-direction: alternate; /* normal, reverse, alternate, alternate-reverse */
  animation-fill-mode: forwards; /* none, forwards, backwards, both */
  animation-play-state: running; /* running, paused */
}
```

## Practical Examples

### Fade In Animation:
```css
@keyframes fadeIn {
  from { opacity: 0; }
  to { opacity: 1; }
}

.fade-in {
  animation: fadeIn 1s ease-in;
}
```

### Bounce Animation:
```css
@keyframes bounce {
  0%, 100% { transform: translateY(0); }
  50% { transform: translateY(-20px); }
}

.bounce {
  animation: bounce 0.6s ease-in-out infinite;
}
```

